summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeThis is pure brightness in a compact that wakes up your face in a swipe. reviews.headline: Love this brightener
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Love the texture of this brightening powder! The finish is flawless! This product had good coverage without being heavy. Very cute packaging also.

reviews.headline: My new favorite brightening powder
reviews.comments: I received this product for free in exchange for my honest review of it. The compact is convenient and lightweight. I have no other products from Fenty, but I really enjoyed this one. I have sensitive, acne prone skin, and this is the perfect blurring powder. Does not irritate my skin and feels nice and light when applying it on my skin. Adds a nice pink to my skin tone, but it isn't overpowering when used correctly. This is a nice, affordable option for a pink setting powder. Highly reccommend!

reviews.headline: A must in your makeup routine!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This product offers both great coverage and texture. The finished look is amazing! The compact design makes it easy to take on the go for emergency touch ups.

reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Love the versatility and compact packaging of this powder. I can't wait throw it in my purse and the little puff is soft, easy to apply. I would like to see other tones like pink

reviews.headline: Perfect for touch ups throughout the day
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I really love the sleek and compact packaging—it feels sturdy and travel-friendly. The powder has a smooth, lightweight texture that blends seamlessly into the skin. The finish is soft and natural with a subtle blurring effect, making pores less noticeable. I appreciate that it brightens without looking chalky or heavy. Coverage is light to medium, perfect for setting concealer or touch-ups throughout the day. There isn't any noticeable scent, which I like since it doesn't clash with other products. Overall, it gives my makeup a polished look while still feeling breathable.

reviews.headline: Bright Fix works great and looks amazing-just a bit pricey.
reviews.comments:
I absolutely love how long this powder lasts and how well it brightens my skin while hiding imperfections. It definitely met my expectations! I have combination skin-not too oily or dry-and this product works beautifully. It gives my skin a soft, radiant look without feeling heavy or cakey. 
The brightening effect is noticeable, and the blurring finish makes my complexion look smooth and even. I would definitely recommend this to anyone looking for a lightweight powder that delivers both glow and coverage. 
The only downside is the price-its a bit on the expensive side. But honestly, it works so well that I still think it's worth it.

reviews.headline: Good but not great
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I don't notice a bright brightening effect but the powder does blur. I use it as a touch up when needed and it does the job. I didn't notice a scent with the product.

reviews.headline: I Suggest Color Matching in Person
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Very cute packaging. Not exactly my skin tone. It's a little too yellow. Very smooth and fine powder so it very weightless. I also don't smell any strong fragrances in it. So far it's pretty good.

reviews.headline: Bright, Smooth and Effortless
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I've been using the Fenty Beauty Bright Fix Instant Brightening & Blurring Powder, and I really like how lightweight and smooth it feels. It instantly brightens my under-eyes without looking cakey, and the blurring effect makes fine lines less noticeable. It holds up well in heat and doesn't crease, but I do have to make sure my under-eyes are well moisturized or it can look a little dry. The compact with the puff is perfect for touch-ups. Shade matching is key though—if you pick the wrong tone, it can look off. Overall, it's a great finishing powder for a fresh, awake look.

reviews.headline: Very nice
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This powder is great! Little to no scent and very soft. The packaging includes a decent sized mirror which i appreciate. I mainly use it under my eyes and it blurs beautifully.

reviews.headline: I like it
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I really like the packaging, it is very beautiful and easy to transport, it lasted all day and leaves a satin finish, not completely matte. I liked it a lot and it has no smell.

The little pad it comes with is worthless lol. Overall I would buy myself to set my makeup.

reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Good quality packaging, and comes with a applicator blotting tool. Also has a mirror inside. I feel it did an okay job at blurring, but hard to tell because the color was wrong for me.

reviews.headline: Blurs and brightens
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This brightening and blurring powder from Fenty it amazing! It provides good coverage and reduces any cakiness from my foundation. Would recommend this product

reviews.headline: It's doing the job
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This blotting and blurring powder is truly incredible at doing its job. It's extended my makeup wear time for up to 12 hours total wear time on a hot, summer day. Though the packaging is a bit bulky for those who prefer a small handbag, I'll always make room for this powder on a steamy night out.

It came with the softest powder, puff to create a soft, blurring brightening finish lavender color, softens any redness or yellowness while he brings out the colors of my eyes I would definitely buy this again. I love Fenty beauty. The only thing I could say is I wish it came with some type of packing brush.

reviews.headline: Long lasting Makeup
reviews.comments: received this product in exchange for my honest review. I have oily skin, and this works really well for keeping shine under control. I love that it's versatile. I use it for quick touch-ups during the day and as a finishing powder. It keeps my makeup in place and helps it last longer. Plus, it comes with a mirror and the compact size makes it super easy to carry in my purse for on-the-go use.

reviews.headline: Bright, Smooth, Natural Finish
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I tried the Bright Fix Instant Brightening + Blurring Powder and it really does give a smooth, soft-focus finish. It brightens my under-eye area without looking cakey and feels super lightweight. The blurring effect is subtle but noticeable—great for a natural look. I just wish it had a bit more lasting power, since I needed to touch up after a few hours.

faceoff_positive.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I was initially on the fence about trying a banana powder, concerned it might leave my skin looking overly yellow. To my surprise, Fenty's take on it was anything but that. The shade "Banana" subtly neutralized the pinkness in my skin and brightened my overall complexion without looking artificial or chalky. The matte finish provides solid coverage while maintaining a smooth, luminous texture that glides on easily and blends seamlessly.

The packaging is one of the standout features. It feels sturdy, reliable, and high-end, with a design that sets it apart from other powders on the market. The clasp closes securely, making it feel well-made and ideal for travel. I especially appreciate the inclusion of a mirror and sponge, which makes on-the-go touch-ups much more convenient.

In terms of performance, I used this powder with nothing underneath but a tinted sunscreen—no primer or setting spray—and it still delivered solid coverage. It did a great job of masking acne and uneven tone, and while it didn't completely hide my deeper under-eye wrinkles (to be fair, most powders won't), it did noticeably brighten the area, which helped me look more refreshed. Bonus points for being fragrance-free, which is always a win for those with sensitive skin.

Throughout a regular workday (about 13 hours of wear), it held up fairly well. Around the end of the day, I noticed some separation and clinging to dry patches, which may have been due to the lack of prep or priming on my part. With better skin prep, I imagine this could be mitigated, so I won't hold that against it.

Overall, this powder exceeded my expectations. It's easy to apply, has great coverage and staying power, and looks beautiful on the skin. While it may need some help in the prep department for very long days, it's a fantastic brightening powder—especially if you're looking for a non-chalky matte finish that works well on sensitive skin.
faceoff_positive.headline: Great Powder

faceoff_negative.comments: Overall I am not a fan of this brightening powder. The color I received was rose quartz 02, which does perfectly match my skin tone so that is a plus. But otherwise I don't see it doing much of anything. The box labels it as a brightening, blurring and finishing powder. I don't really see any signs of instant brightening that is claimed and I only see maybe a little bit of blurring some of my pores. But even that is only really noticeable on parts of my face that tend to be oilier than others, like on my nose. But it is not enough overall to make me want to add it to my supply or replace something else. Especially given the other issues, with the compact itself. The first is it is a thick plastic, that looks cheap and makes me think of one those kids makeup kits. The only good thing being is that it does latch close tightly so you are unlikely to have it accidentally open. The next issue is with the mirror, first being that it looks sort of poorly inlaid into the compact like someone just stuck glue on a mirror and put it in. I feel like with little effort I could pop it out. The mirror also has the brand name in bold black on the bottom edge of the mirror. Which is just extremely annoying, especially if you are out and can only use that mirror. It is a small mirror so it is very easy for your eyes to focus on the text over your face when trying to apply it. The next issue is the applicator pad it comes with. Personally I would throw it away and replace it with your own or a different brush. The back is a leather or fake leather like material, with the brand name on it. The biggest issue is unlike a lot of puffs that are soft and easily flexible, with the puff part covering the sides, this has none of that. The edge is sharpness from the leathery plastic it is made of. Which while applying don't expect any precision while trying to apply near the edge, it will hurt and felt like I could potentially give myself something like a paper cut on my face with it. The corners are also hard and it is very easy to have them accidentally gouge into the powder block. I just don't see enough benefit with this product to justify recommending it. Maybe other people with different skin types will see more benefit, but I would see if you can test it in store first before buying it.
faceoff_negative.headline: Too many issues, too little benefit
